node.text: This episode of #PastriesWithPaola, features a Guava and Cheese Bread Pudding that Paola Velez (@smallorchids) calls "history in a bowl." This particular budin de pan recipe originated with her husband's 101-year-old grandmother, and features a lavish custard base, two ways to make homemade caramel, and a finish of chopped fresh mango for an optional garnish. Misu the Bodega Cat joins in for an inspired, fun culinary adventure. New episodes premiere every Wednesday. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

This Cracked Shrimp with Pineapple-Habanero Relish recipe is @carlaphall’s take on Bahamian cracked conch. Flattening each shrimp with a rolling pin yields tender, extra-crispy results. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!
📸: @gregdupree

node.text:
These chicken cutlets in a light, Parm-infused batter, and simmered in a lemony, chickeny cream sauce are an Italian-American red-sauce restaurant classic, paired perfectly with a crisp arugula salad or sauteed green beans. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
🍗: @jazzy_the_princess 📸: @jencausey

node.text:
Lemon zest, vanilla, and maple syrup add sweetness to the light and fluffy Quinoa Pancakes with Ricotta and Lemon recipe. Due to the clever addition of whipped egg whites, these light pancakes are a welcome addition to any menu. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
🥞: @paigegrandjean 📸: @antonisachilleos

node.text: In this episode of Chefs At Home, @meherwanirani of @chaipani and @spicewalla makes Spicy Green Banana Cutlets (Kaera Na Cutless), a traditional Parsi dish. Toasted spices, mashed green bananas, and panko come together to create these crispy, crunchy croquettes. Tap the link in our bio to watch the full episode on YouTube and get the recipe!

node.text:
Enriched with ripe tomatoes, cherries, and Italian peppers, this velvety smooth Cherry Gazpacho recipe is garnished with anchovies, basil oil, and pistachios for texture with a dusting of goat cheese for tanginess. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
🍒: @vonbremzen 📸: @christophertestani

node.text: Fresh and freeze-dried berries meld in this Strawberry Cupcakes with Cream Cheese Frosting recipe for the ultimate summer treat. Lemon zest and buttermilk make the cupcakes tangy and fresh while the sweet cream cheese frosting keeps them moist and tender. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍓: @paigegrandjean 📸: @jencausey

node.text: Golden brown garlic, melted butter, a splash of vermouth, and Worcestershire are combined in a savory, velvety sauce that coats each of these steak bites to deliver a luxury of a steakhouse-caliber dish at home. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 🥩: @mariannew44

node.text:
This ultra-rich Hong Kong Milk Tea Tiramisu is subtly sweet and well balanced by the lightly bitter tannins in the Hong Kong milk tea powder. A garnish of finely grated milk chocolate makes this dessert complete. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
🍽️: @chefmelissaking 📸: @chelsealouisekyle

node.text: Juicy roasted bell peppers bring the sweet, and spicy pepper paste brings the heat to this Muhammara (Roasted Red Pepper and Walnut Dip) recipe. Pomegranate molasses and toasted walnuts add depth to this smooth, thick, and mildly spicy dip. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍽️: @jeanettechawki 📸: @protazio
